 tend to use basically four different sources of carbon}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs22\lang2057\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s17\cf1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs34\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0 Carbon (and more specifically, particular types of coal) is a suitable reductant for use in a pyro-metallurgical environment.}}}
{\*\cs34\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up9\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af11\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177\cf3 }{\cf3  to act as reductants in the reduction of metal oxide to metal, namely coke, char, anthracite and bituminous coal. These vary according to price and efficacy; the more effective a reductant, the more 
